11/07/2007
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat announced on Tuesday (July 10th) that he accepted an invitation from Greek Cypriot President Tassos Papadopoulos for a meeting aimed at reviving reunification talks. Talat told a news conference that he views the invitation as a "positive step". No specific date has been mentioned, though the meeting is expected before the end of July. (Zaman, Politis - 11/07/07; NTV, CNA - 10/07/07)
